## 3. **Shopify (SHOP) â€“ A slow steady rise, long sideways consolidation, then explosive growth**

* **Modest IPO pop:** Shopify priced at **USâ€¯\$17/share** in **MayÂ 2015**, rising \~50% on the first dayâ€”solid, but not dramatic ([time.com][8]).
* **Extended consolidation:** From midâ€‘2018 through late 2018, Shopifyâ€™s stock pulled back \~33% into a messy, multiâ€‘week consolidation pattern (not a classic base), frustrating many traders ([investors.com][9]).
* **Massive breakout:** After clearing the consolidation buyâ€‘point in **December 2018**, the stock rallied \~236% by August 2019, and continued soaringâ€”returning over **2,200â€“2,600% from IPO-levels** through 2025 ([fool.ca][10], [seekingalpha.com][11]).

ğŸ¯ **Insight:** Sometimes the most explosive winners donâ€™t start with big first-day movesâ€”they build structural bases, then erupt as fundamentals align.

